name: Foot Loose (VAGABOND)
aboutt: It is a competition between duos, and solos. The song will be played on the spot and the participant has to perform impromptu on the same song. There'll be elimination rounds between 2 participants at a time, solo competing with solo and duo with duo. The judges panel will score the performances on various aspects and will decide the Winner and 1 st Runner up, in each category.

name: FEST IN BEATS
aboutt: It is a competition between teams, duos, and solos. There will be no elimination rounds. The judges panel will score the performances on various aspects and will decide the Winner, 1st Runner up & 2nd Runner up.

name: CRESENDO
aboutt:
The competition will let the students compete under 6 categories:INDIAN SOLO | WESTERN SOLO | DUET | INSTRUMENTAL | GROUP| RAPPING+BEATBOXING CRESCENDO
willbeorganized in two phases. ? ROUND 1: 2-3 minutes performances, the qualifying round ROUND 2: 3-5 minutes to perform under their categories and jury based on certain aspects like Rhythm/Pitch, Grip on vocals, etc.

name: MOCK THE PARLIAMENT-(LC)
about: A fun parliament session where groups will evd on some entertaining topics.

name: PANEL OF ASPIRANST'S
about: The event is a replication of GD Round that is taken in Service Selection Board of Defence Services Recruitments. The panel consists of Senior Army Personnel who will convene the event.The discussion offers positive and negative perspectives on how academic and background diversity affects the students and aspirants and enhances competitiveness, creative approach, and effectiveness in defense recruitment and retention.The event aims to develop communication skills, how to interrupt a speaking member without using his/her first language, and how to speak in front of Rank Officers (Defense  Personnel).Content: Panel will address the topic of the Group Discussion related to Defense Current Affairs and participants must propose and put forward their take in favor or against. The challenge is to convince the Judging panel and the participants of the Group Discussion to put arguments and facts with precision in front of everyone so that at the end of the event all the members come to one arbitrament.
Overall Head: U.O Lokesh Rawat, SGT. Ankit Raj Kumawat, Cdt. Devansh Ahi,
Coordinator: U.O Lokesh Rawat, SGT. Ankit Raj Kumawat, Cdt. Devansh Ahi

name: VAAD VIVAD
about: Vaad vivad is a evd competition in which the participants discuss a topic from two opposing sides. Those who agree with this statement or idea are on the 'for' side. Those who will not agree with this statement or idea are on the 'against' side.

name: Film Making
about: The event will focus on theater. Participants will make a short film and will be judged on the basis of acting, storyline, and direction.

name: Badshah-e-Manch
about: Event will have participants performing solo acts.

name: Dekha-Dekhi
about: In this event, participants will be given chits with famous characters written on them. Participants will have to enact the character they get.

name: IPL Bidding
about: Participants will be given certain currency points to create the best IPL team. IPL players will have different ratings. highest rating team will win the game.

name: Tug-of-War
about: Each team consists of eight people. The rope used should be of a circumference of approx 11 cm and should be marked in the middle with a center line as well as two marks that should be placed 4m from the center line. The team that pulls the other team beyond the mark wins the round.

name: MURDER MYSTERY
about: In this murder mystery game, guests take the roles of various cast and crew members celebrating the completion of filming of their movie when the Director suddenly dies at the party. However, the paranoid Director hid magical clues. These clues reveal as to who committed the crime. The party's story, the movie itself, and the characters are improvised, making it different each time it's played with between 5 and 10 people.

name: DIT ROADIES
about: Participants will be given series of fun tasks, first one to complete will win the game.

name: GULLY CRICKET
about: This will be a game of gully cricket

name: 3-D GLOBE
about: A big model to be displayed of a GLOBE consisting of a collage of all the events conducted by the DIT University.

name: TUG OF WAR
about: Each team consists of eight people. The rope used should be of a circumference of approx 11 cm and should be marked in the middle with a center line as well as two marks that should be placed 4m from the center line.

name: BEST OUT OF WASTE
about: It will be an Inter-University Competition. Group of participants (maximum 4) from different universities will bring their semi- prepared products made from waste. 1hr will be given to them to complete their and product and they will be asked to describe their products the jury will mark then on the basis of creativity and product presentation. There will be exciting prizes for the winners and runner-ups.

name: DART GAME
about: Darts, indoor target game played by throwing feathered darts at a circular board with numbered spaces.

name: ARM WRESTLING
about: It is an event that will test your strength. The team that pins the other person wins the round.

name: RING SHOT
about: Ring toss is a game in which the object is to toss a ring so that it will fall over an upright stick.

name: 7 UP 7 DOWN
about: 7 Up 7 Down is a simple dice game that provides only three basic betting options

name: DOUBLE THE MONEY
about: The rules will be mentioned on the spot, during the event.

name: KAI PO CHE
about: Flying colourful kites with your buddies under the morning sun from a rooftop or ground is an unbeatable experience and a relaxing hobby. There will be exciting prizes for the winners and runner-ups

name: SLOW & STEADY
about: This game consists of 3 challengers each with a toilet paper roll and a glass on it then the player has to pull the glass towards himself whosever pulls the glass first wins the game

name: BLIND RACE
about: The game will comprise of two pairs, where 1 member from each pair will be blindfolded, and the other will guide the blind to the finish line avoiding the obstacles

name: TREASURE HUNT
about: Participants will have to solve series of clues to find the treasure.

name: RAMP WALK
about: It's the grace with which you walk.

name: Retrospect
about: The Event will be arcade styled i.e., initially the event will be Player vs Player, player who wins will continue to play unless he/she gets defeated.

name: Sherlocked 5.0
about: Several adventurous phases where the teams will be allowed to roam the entire campus and look for treasure items (to find hidden objects/places). Each clue will have a particular story plot question which needs to be answered to solve a particular level.

name: Fly Through
about: Obstacle drone racing is a test of pilot's ability to beat other competitors by racing around specially built courses by crossing various obstacles to reach the finish line in the fastest time. Pilots may practice at the designated practice fields before the event. Limited practice runs would be provided to the participants. The participants are supposed to cross various hurdles such as Hula Hoops, Balloons etc. while flying the drone in order for the drones to reach the finish line.

name: Code with Arduino
about: Coding with Arduino would put your critical thinking and evt skills in the same boat. In this event a participant has to design an Arduino circuit according to a given problem statement. An on-spot designing contest, an open-ended problem statement will be provided for the registered groups for which they are expected to design an Arduino circuit (which meets the requirements). Participants are expected to Implement the Arduino circuit design.

name: Code-2-Win
about: It will be an exciting event as the name suggests CODE2WIN to challenge the evt skills within a particular given time. Participants will have the option of choosing either of the three difficulty levels (Easy, Medium, Hard) and within a specific time frame they have to solve either one question for winning a single prize or solve 2 Questions for winning double prizes.Questions will test the coding ability of participants at various difficulty levels. There will be exciting rewards such as amazon vouchers, goodies etc.
